        <type><ref refid="struct_x_i_o_module___config" kindref="compound">XIOModule_Config</ref></type>
        <definition>XIOModule_Config XIOModule_ConfigTable[XPAR_XIOMODULE_NUM_INSTANCES]</definition>
        <argsstring>[XPAR_XIOMODULE_NUM_INSTANCES]</argsstring>
        <name>XIOModule_ConfigTable</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This table contains configuration information for each iomodule device in the system. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The <ref refid="struct_x_i_o_module" kindref="compound">XIOModule</ref> driver must know when to acknowledge the interrupt. The entry which specifies this as a bit mask where each bit corresponds to a specific interrupt. A bit set indicates to ack it before servicing it. Generally, acknowledge before service is used when the interrupt signal is edge-sensitive, and after when the signal is level-sensitive.</para><para>Refer to the <ref refid="struct_x_i_o_module___config" kindref="compound">XIOModule_Config</ref> data structure in <ref refid="xiomodule_8h" kindref="compound">xiomodule.h</ref> for details on how this table should be initialized. </para>        </detaileddescription>
